The Governor of Niger State, Abubakar Sani Bello has confirmed his position as the acting chairman of the Caretaker/Extra-ordinary Convention Planning Committee of the ruling All Progressives Congress.Bello stated this on Monday while addressing journalists at the APC National Headquarters, Abuja. The governor also informed journalists that a date has been fixed for the convention — March 26, 2022 He said, “We discussed progress with regards to our convention and what needs to be done next. I am the acting chairman. I have been acting for a while now since the chairman travelled.”Meanwhile, Bello presided over a meeting of the CECPC on Monday, according to photos he shared on his Twitter handle. The governor was seen seated in what appears to be the position meant for the Chairman of the APC-CECPC, Governor Mai Bala Muni of Yobe State.He tweeted, “I am currently presiding over the Caretaker/Extra-ordinary Convention Planning Committee of the APC at the National Secretariat of the Party.”https://twitter.com/abusbello/status/1500810468981620740?t=nq3Ee5sDR3YLjbShYzms7w&s=19The development comes amid a rumoured crisis plaguing the leadership of the APC.According to reports, President Muhammadu Buhari allegedly approved the removal of the Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni, as the Chairman of the CECPC and in his stead, appointed Bello. Niger State Governor Sani Bello has just confirmed his position as the acting chairman of the APC @OfficialAPCNg The governor also confirmed that there will be a convention for the scheduled date of March 26, 2022 pic.twitter.com/NyNxudiTcY 